I can't do it without you.

492
00:42:00,920 --> 00:42:03,080
- It's a 55 zone.
- What?

493
00:42:03,120 --> 00:42:05,480
If you drive any faster,
this heap will blow up.

494
00:42:05,560 --> 00:42:07,120
This is not a heap.

495
00:42:07,240 --> 00:42:10,480
This is a 1974 Cadillac,
bought and paid for by yours truly.

496
00:42:10,480 --> 00:42:13,600
- Nice color too.
- It's a cool color. It's a cool car.

497
00:42:13,600 --> 00:42:15,400
Can you say that, Victor?
"Cool"?

498
00:42:15,520 --> 00:42:18,120
I can say "70 miles an hour. "
I can say that.

499
00:42:18,160 --> 00:42:20,640
Well, then... why don't you drive?

500
00:42:20,720 --> 00:42:23,560
No! Please don't do that.
I can't. I can't drive. Hilary.

501
00:42:23,640 --> 00:42:26,240
- Are you kidding me?
- Thank you for your compassion.

502
00:42:26,320 --> 00:42:28,560
I'm sorry.

503
00:42:28,600 --> 00:42:31,360
My father had a driver.
I never learned how.

504
00:42:31,440 --> 00:42:34,600
- I think it's time you started to learn.
- No, please don't do that!

505
00:42:34,640 --> 00:42:36,440
- It's cool, huh?
- Take... Take the wheel.

506
00:42:36,560 --> 00:42:39,400
I'm helping you. I'm helping you
stay between the lines.

507
00:42:39,480 --> 00:42:42,240
There you go.
You're doing fine. There you go.

508
00:43:25,920 --> 00:43:28,600
<i>- I know why you like it here.
- Why?</i>

509
00:43:28,680 --> 00:43:31,400
<i>- 'Cause all these buildings
have dates on them.</i>

510
00:43:32,680 --> 00:43:35,800
Oh, look at that.
Don't look. Watch the road.

511
00:43:41,520 --> 00:43:44,400
- Goin' a little fast?
- What?

512
00:43:44,480 --> 00:43:47,960
I'm kidding.
You're driving, like, 23 miles an hour.

513
00:43:48,920 --> 00:43:50,800
Scared you?

514
00:44:09,960 --> 00:44:12,120
Thank you.

515
00:44:29,440 --> 00:44:31,240
Oh, look. Hi!

516
00:44:31,360 --> 00:44:33,840
<i>Wejust moved in!</i>

517
00:44:38,200 --> 00:44:40,760
Kind and friendly neighbor.

518
00:44:58,400 --> 00:45:00,200
Here, let me get that.

519
00:45:00,320 --> 00:45:02,520
- It's okay.
- It's okay.

520
00:45:09,000 --> 00:45:10,880
You okay?

521
00:45:32,680 --> 00:45:34,560
So beautiful.

522
00:45:42,160 --> 00:45:43,920
What is this?

523
00:45:44,080 --> 00:45:46,680
Those are ampules of morphine.

524
00:45:47,960 --> 00:45:51,200
<i>- For pain.
- Isn't a doctor supposed to do this?</i>

525
00:45:51,200 --> 00:45:54,360
Oh, I know precisely what to do.

526
00:45:55,320 --> 00:45:57,120
Years of experience.

527
00:45:57,240 --> 00:45:59,920
<i>- Do you need one?
- No, I won't need one.</i>

528
00:45:59,960 --> 00:46:02,840
Put them away.
I won't need one.

529
00:46:23,400 --> 00:46:25,200
Oh, I'm sorry.

530
00:46:25,320 --> 00:46:27,720
No, it's okay. I'm done.

531
00:47:16,720 --> 00:47:18,520
Come on.

532
00:47:18,640 --> 00:47:20,520
- They'll start by staring.
- No, they won't.

533
00:47:20,640 --> 00:47:23,040
Someone will ask,
"Hey, man, why ain't you got any hair?"

534
00:47:23,120 --> 00:47:25,760
- They'll be too busy drinking.
- I've been to places like this. They always ask.

535
00:47:25,840 --> 00:47:27,600
- Come on.
- They always ask.

536
00:47:37,040 --> 00:47:39,200
Two beers.

537
00:47:44,480 --> 00:47:46,880
Thanks. Save the glasses.

538
00:47:49,560 --> 00:47:52,240
- You moved into Demazian's place?
- Uh-huh.

539
00:47:52,320 --> 00:47:54,160
Bring your foul-weather gear?

540
00:47:54,280 --> 00:47:57,520
Geez, you're gonna fuckin'
freeze to death up there.

541
00:47:57,520 --> 00:47:59,880
Weather-strip it. That'll fix it.

542
00:47:59,960 --> 00:48:03,000
<i>I've weather-stripped
around 30 houses. Works every time.</i>

543
00:48:03,000 --> 00:48:06,240
You mean you stripped
in about 30 houses.

544
00:48:08,600 --> 00:48:10,400
Anyway, I'd do yours.

545
00:48:10,520 --> 00:48:12,520
- Cappy.
- Hilary.

546
00:48:12,560 --> 00:48:14,360
- Thank you.
- Victor.

547
00:48:14,480 --> 00:48:16,280
How do you do?

548
00:48:16,400 --> 00:48:19,400
<i>Hilary, beer's on the house.</i>

549
00:48:19,360 --> 00:48:22,800
<i>- You're kidding!
- So, Vic, how come you shaved your head?</i>

550
00:48:24,240 --> 00:48:26,040
Yeah.

551
00:48:26,160 --> 00:48:28,840
He's a Hare Krishna.

552
00:48:28,880 --> 00:48:31,760
- No, you know, at the airport, the guys in the yellow...
- Saffron.

553
00:48:31,840 --> 00:48:34,240
- Robes, passing out flowers.
- Daisies.

554
00:48:34,320 --> 00:48:38,040
- Take off.
- With his little cymbals, singing.

555
00:48:39,720 --> 00:48:41,880
- Sing.
- What?

556
00:48:41,960 --> 00:48:44,280
- Sing, hon.
- Yeah, give us a few notes.

557
00:48:44,320 --> 00:48:46,800
No, I can't.
I can't.

558
00:48:46,880 --> 00:48:49,120
- I left the order.
- Come on, come on.

559
00:48:49,160 --> 00:48:52,720
- I gave back my robe and cymbals.
- Why?

560
00:48:52,760 --> 00:48:55,040
Because the order is celibate.
We're like priests.

561
00:48:55,080 --> 00:48:57,480
<i>- No kidding.
- Yes. Stricter, really.</i>

562
00:48:57,560 --> 00:49:01,920
And, uh, I shouldn't be
telling you this, but...

563
00:49:01,880 --> 00:49:05,520
- That's all right. We're good for it.
- Very private.

564
00:49:05,520 --> 00:49:07,800
Well, the truth is,
Hilary came along.

565
00:49:07,840 --> 00:49:11,200
I was at the airport, at United, which,
as you know, is the best location.

566
00:49:11,200 --> 00:49:13,640
And, uh, I was stopping people...

567
00:49:13,680 --> 00:49:16,400
giving them a flower and saying,
"God is love. Have a nice day. "

568
00:49:16,480 --> 00:49:18,640
Then I stopped Hilary.

569
00:49:20,560 --> 00:49:23,000
She turned to me, and I knew.

570
00:49:23,080 --> 00:49:26,480
I stopped shaving my head the next day,
and we got in the car and came here.

571
00:49:26,480 --> 00:49:29,160
Probably her favorite
vacation spot. Right, hon?

572
00:49:35,120 --> 00:49:38,480
<i>Nah!</i>

573
00:49:38,520 --> 00:49:41,000
- No, no, no, no.
- Nice try, kid.

574
00:49:41,080 --> 00:49:43,400
That'll be 2.50 for the beer.

575
00:49:46,280 --> 00:49:49,960
That's good. That's real good.

576
00:50:01,240 --> 00:50:03,040
Are you okay?

577
00:50:05,120 --> 00:50:07,320
Do you need me?

578
00:50:12,680 --> 00:50:14,480
<i>Sorry.</i>

579
00:50:14,600 --> 00:50:18,360
Yes, I need, uh...

580
00:50:20,960 --> 00:50:22,760
I can't sleep.

581
00:50:25,000 --> 00:50:27,840
I, uh...

582
00:50:27,920 --> 00:50:30,320
I need to, uh, lie down...

583
00:50:30,360 --> 00:50:32,920
Next to you.

584
00:50:33,000 --> 00:50:35,080
I mean, I need to...

585
00:50:35,080 --> 00:50:38,240
I want to sleep... in your bed.

586
00:50:38,280 --> 00:50:42,760
<i>Not... Believe me, I'm no threat.
Not after the chemotherapy. I just can't...</i>

587
00:50:42,760 --> 00:50:47,280
This is not part of the deal.
Tell me to leave.

588
00:50:49,480 --> 00:50:51,480
No, it's okay.

589
00:50:55,200 --> 00:50:57,360
Okay.

590
00:51:26,400 --> 00:51:28,920
What does your tattoo mean?

591
00:51:31,400 --> 00:51:34,160
Strength of heart.

592
00:51:40,280 --> 00:51:43,080
- Good morning.
- Morning.

593
00:51:43,280 --> 00:51:46,080
- If I drink this, can I have a cigarette?
- No.

594
00:51:46,280 --> 00:51:50,000
No, I didn't think so.
Wait a minute. Show you something.

595
00:51:50,160 --> 00:51:52,920
Feel it. Feel it.

596
00:51:54,720 --> 00:51:56,960
- It's coming in.
- Yeah.

597
00:51:57,080 --> 00:52:00,200
- No fever. Is there?
- No.

598
00:52:02,480 --> 00:52:04,280
Uh, wait a second.

599
00:52:06,160 --> 00:52:09,240
- I have an idea.
- That's okay.

600
00:52:09,360 --> 00:52:12,560
- I'd like to tell you about it, but...
- But what?

601
00:52:12,680 --> 00:52:15,760
- But don't get mad.
- Why?

602
00:52:15,880 --> 00:52:18,640
Well, it has something
to do with...

603
00:52:18,840 --> 00:52:20,880
something you're sensitive about.

604
00:52:20,960 --> 00:52:23,320
My cooking? My clothing? My hair?

605
00:52:23,440 --> 00:52:25,560
Your education.

606
00:52:25,720 --> 00:52:28,320
You know, I have spent
my entire life studying.

607
00:52:28,480 --> 00:52:31,040
Years of lying in a bed reading.
Not what you were doing.

608
00:52:31,200 --> 00:52:33,960
- Sleeping with construction workers.
- No. Living.

609
00:52:34,120 --> 00:52:38,240
I am trying to learn a bit about that from
you, and I want to give you something back.

610
00:52:38,400 --> 00:52:41,520
To, uh, teach you.
Not school, but, uh...

611
00:52:41,640 --> 00:52:43,800
I see in you...

612
00:52:43,960 --> 00:52:47,040
I don't care about
your little jokes or anything.

613
00:52:47,160 --> 00:52:49,200
I see interest...

614
00:52:49,280 --> 00:52:51,800
<i>about things.</i>

615
00:52:53,360 --> 00:52:55,800
Tell me I'm wrong.
Tell me to go to hell.

616
00:52:55,920 --> 00:52:59,520
- Go to hell.
- Tell me you're not interested.

617
00:53:01,560 --> 00:53:03,840
What would you teach me?

618
00:53:04,000 --> 00:53:07,760
Uh, well, you like Klimt, right?
We start with a book on modern art.

619
00:53:08,000 --> 00:53:10,440
<i>You take a look at it, you read it.</i>

620
00:53:10,640 --> 00:53:11,760
<i>Then, uh, we talk. That's all.</i>

621
00:53:13,760 --> 00:53:17,280
Damn it. I know I do that.
You can hit me if I start.

622
00:53:17,320 --> 00:53:20,160
<i>I mean it. Strike me. Humble me.</i>

623
00:53:20,240 --> 00:53:22,240
I will.

624
00:54:05,400 --> 00:54:08,400
My hair looks good.
Don't touch my hair.

625
00:54:32,880 --> 00:54:35,360
<i>Read 'em and weep.</i>

626
00:54:38,480 --> 00:54:40,200
<i>- Check.
- Check.</i>

627
00:54:40,360 --> 00:54:42,600
<i>- I'll bet.
- Oh, man, you got nothin'.</i>

628
00:54:42,640 --> 00:54:45,320
<i>- Go fish.
- Hon, hon, you have zippo.</i>

629
00:54:45,360 --> 00:54:47,640
<i>- Two dollars.
- Oh, come on!</i>

630
00:54:47,680 --> 00:54:50,040
<i>You're bluffing.</i>

631
00:54:50,080 --> 00:54:52,200
Put up or shut up.

632
00:54:52,240 --> 00:54:55,440
<i>- Two bucks. Cards for the players.
- I'm in.</i>

633
00:54:55,440 --> 00:54:58,200
I think they should
just change the rules.

634
00:54:58,240 --> 00:55:01,880
For instance, you get like partial
credit for a four... a four-card flush.

635
00:55:01,920 --> 00:55:04,680
<i>Especially if you have an ace.
I had an ace. It was the best ace.</i>

636
00:55:04,760 --> 00:55:07,480
The biggest ace.
The ace of spades. It was fan...

637
00:55:07,560 --> 00:55:11,400
A big, bold card, and it deserves
to beat a pair of deuces.

638
00:55:13,520 --> 00:55:15,520
You want to dance?

639
00:55:15,560 --> 00:55:18,800
You really are well,
aren't you, Victor?

640
00:55:18,800 --> 00:55:20,880
Yes, thanks to you.

641
00:55:26,360 --> 00:55:28,520
<i>What?</i>

642
00:55:28,560 --> 00:55:33,760
I don't know. Um...
it feels like the deal's over.

643
00:55:33,680 --> 00:55:35,360
What do you mean?

644
00:55:35,480 --> 00:55:37,520
<i>Well, like, the chemo's done
and you're better...</i>

645
00:55:37,560 --> 00:55:41,120
and, uh... I'm still taking money.

646
00:55:41,120 --> 00:55:43,680
<i>- That's okay.
- It doesn't feel right.</i>

647
00:55:43,760 --> 00:55:46,280
Maybe we should just go back.

648
00:55:46,360 --> 00:55:50,920
Back? Why would you
want to go back?

649
00:55:52,440 --> 00:55:56,080
Well, I-I feel like there's
no job here for me anymore.

650
00:55:57,760 --> 00:55:59,800
Is there?

651
00:56:12,560 --> 00:56:14,680
I guess not.

652
00:56:18,320 --> 00:56:20,720
Okay.

653
00:56:22,800 --> 00:56:24,600
<i>Good night.</i>

654
00:56:24,720 --> 00:56:26,760
Good night.

655
00:57:15,160 --> 00:57:17,640
Mmm. Hi.

656
00:58:31,680 --> 00:58:34,240
I have a confession to make.

657
00:58:36,800 --> 00:58:39,200
- You awake?
- No.

658
00:58:39,240 --> 00:58:42,880
Good. Then it'll be easier.

659
00:58:42,880 --> 00:58:44,720
I lied.

660
00:58:47,480 --> 00:58:50,360
There were never any
other women in my house.

661
00:58:51,800 --> 00:58:54,280
That's okay. I lied too.

662
00:58:54,320 --> 00:58:58,680
I was never vice president
of the Future Nurses of America.

663
00:59:08,000 --> 00:59:10,520
What about the picture
of you and that girl?

664
00:59:10,560 --> 00:59:13,240
- What picture?
- The one in your apartment.

665
00:59:13,320 --> 00:59:16,000
Jean. Jean.

666
00:59:17,920 --> 00:59:19,760
College.

667
00:59:21,680 --> 00:59:23,840
She was...

668
00:59:23,840 --> 00:59:27,680
I was in remission and...

669
00:59:27,680 --> 00:59:29,840
we were in love, I guess.

670
00:59:29,880 --> 00:59:32,400
I don't know.

671
00:59:32,440 --> 00:59:36,240
I got sick, she left.

672
00:59:39,960 --> 00:59:43,040
Now you're leaving
because I'm well.

673
00:59:43,040 --> 00:59:47,400
No. I just told you I don't want
to take your money anymore.

674
00:59:47,360 --> 00:59:49,640
Okay, no more money.

675
00:59:51,680 --> 00:59:54,440
I have to give you
something then.

676
00:59:54,520 --> 00:59:58,160
Mmm. No more art history
lessons, please.

677
00:59:59,480 --> 01:00:02,160
Well...

678
01:00:02,240 --> 01:00:05,440
then I have only
one thing to give you.

679
01:00:08,360 --> 01:00:10,160
My heart.

680
01:00:14,920 --> 01:00:17,040
You can have my heart.

681
01:00:22,920 --> 01:00:25,240
I couldn't say that before.

682
01:00:25,280 --> 01:00:28,320
You can't say that
to someone when you're sick.

683
01:00:28,280 --> 01:00:30,880
Yes, you can.

684
01:00:30,960 --> 01:00:33,760
I love you, Hilary...

685
01:00:33,840 --> 01:00:36,640
and I don't want you to leave.

686
01:00:44,240 --> 01:00:47,840
You don't have to say anything.
It's all right.

687
01:00:51,160 --> 01:00:53,560
I do have to say something.

688
01:00:56,320 --> 01:00:58,520
I want to...

689
01:01:00,320 --> 01:01:02,560
I want to say, um...

690
01:01:05,200 --> 01:01:09,640
You're a pain in the ass.

691
01:01:09,600 --> 01:01:13,400
But I know the sweetness in you,
and I know that you've changed me.

692
01:01:16,400 --> 01:01:18,960
And I want to say...

693
01:01:21,040 --> 01:01:23,120
thank you.

694
01:01:26,720 --> 01:01:29,440
I won't leave you.

695
01:01:30,760 --> 01:01:33,560
Oh! It's cold!

696
01:01:50,320 --> 01:01:53,120
Never dare a Geddes.

697
01:01:58,280 --> 01:02:01,000
Good morning, Mrs. Merkel.

698
01:03:13,680 --> 01:03:17,680
<i>Hello? Anybody home?</i>

699
01:03:17,680 --> 01:03:19,760
<i>Hello?</i>

700
01:03:20,920 --> 01:03:23,720
- Hey. Time to strip the windows.
- Hi.

701
01:03:23,800 --> 01:03:26,400
Sorry I've been so long.

702
01:03:26,480 --> 01:03:29,920
I've been working up at this winery
for this old lady, making barrels.

703
01:03:29,920 --> 01:03:34,520
<i>She's crazy. She's got three husbands
buried out there.</i>

704
01:03:34,520 --> 01:03:38,600
And she reads tea leaves.
I'm not kiddin'.

705
01:03:38,560 --> 01:03:40,880
She's crazy.
You gotta meet her.

706
01:03:40,920 --> 01:03:45,240
Here's where your problem is.
Comes right off the water and right in.

707
01:03:45,200 --> 01:03:47,000
Feel.

708
01:03:48,480 --> 01:03:50,240
- Feel it?
- Mm-hmm.

709
01:03:50,360 --> 01:03:53,560
- Hello, Gordon.
- Vic! Hey!

710
01:03:53,560 --> 01:03:56,080
<i>- Hi. How are you doing?
- All right.</i>

711
01:03:56,160 --> 01:03:58,440
Uh... what are you doing?

712
01:03:58,480 --> 01:04:00,840
I got a surprise.

713
01:04:07,840 --> 01:04:11,320
- Well, it is freezing in here.
- Mm-hmm.

714
01:04:11,360 --> 01:04:14,160
Call me insane,
but I'd venture a guess...

715
01:04:14,240 --> 01:04:17,040
that Gordon would like to
warm you up in any way possible.

716
01:04:25,360 --> 01:04:27,600
Cappy told me
you didn't have a TV set.

717
01:04:27,640 --> 01:04:29,520
Yes. Uh, no.

718
01:04:29,640 --> 01:04:32,640
<i>I guess we never... ever...</i>

719
01:04:32,640 --> 01:04:34,680
Well, it's only black and white.

720
01:04:34,760 --> 01:04:37,360
I don't use it, so...

721
01:04:37,440 --> 01:04:40,480
- Oh, I, uh...
- Here.

722
01:04:40,480 --> 01:04:42,640
I'll put it on the table.

723
01:04:42,680 --> 01:04:44,480
<i>Oh, cripes.</i>

724
01:04:44,600 --> 01:04:48,240
"Cripes"?

725
01:04:48,280 --> 01:04:50,520
Be careful. God.

726
01:04:52,320 --> 01:04:55,720
- Oh, no. It works.

727
01:04:55,760 --> 01:04:57,600
<i>Thanks, Gordon.</i>

728
01:04:57,720 --> 01:05:03,120
I don't think... We're not really
very big, uh, television watchers here.

729
01:05:03,040 --> 01:05:05,360
But thanks. We're not, uh...

730
01:05:05,400 --> 01:05:07,960
- What is nectar?
- Absolutely right.

731
01:05:08,000 --> 01:05:10,040
<i>- Oh, wait.
- TheJetsons!</i>

732
01:05:10,080 --> 01:05:12,600
<i>- Are you a big fan of TheJetsons now?
- Go back one.</i>

733
01:05:12,640 --> 01:05:15,400
- Belle of Amherst.
- Emily Dickinson.

734
01:05:15,480 --> 01:05:17,600
- Duncan.
- Who is Emily Dickinson?

735
