01:21:43,080 --> 01:21:45,160
<i>Sitcoms, Victor.
Come on. Like Mr. Ed.</i>

972
01:21:45,200 --> 01:21:48,600
<i>Shakespeare. That's a sitcom.
She Stoops to Conquer. Oliver Goldsmith.</i>

973
01:21:48,640 --> 01:21:51,360
<i>- This is no English class!
- They're all situationally comic.</i>

974
01:21:51,440 --> 01:21:55,480
Hils, what is he doing? What are you
doing, Victor? For Christ's sakes.

975
01:21:55,440 --> 01:21:58,440
<i>Jesus, come on!
Nine. All right. Nine.</i>

976
01:21:58,440 --> 01:22:01,800
Nine!

977
01:22:01,800 --> 01:22:04,120
Hello! Hello in there!

978
01:22:04,160 --> 01:22:06,400
Gordon, don't.

979
01:22:06,440 --> 01:22:10,040
Number of players
on a baseball team, Gordo.

980
01:22:10,120 --> 01:22:12,600
<i>Here, let me help him.</i>

981
01:22:15,040 --> 01:22:17,680
All right. Okay.

982
01:22:23,240 --> 01:22:27,720
Just take it easy, Victor.
You'll be all right.

983
01:22:27,720 --> 01:22:30,320
<i>Come on. You'll sleep it off.</i>

984
01:22:30,400 --> 01:22:33,840
<i>Put your head down.
You'll be okay.</i>

985
01:22:44,400 --> 01:22:47,520
<i>Sorry I brought the bottle.
I didn't know that, uh...</i>

986
01:22:47,520 --> 01:22:50,520
- Neither did I.
- If I can do anything...

987
01:22:52,200 --> 01:22:54,200
Good night.

988
01:22:56,080 --> 01:22:59,600
Um, remember, if you need me...

989
01:22:59,640 --> 01:23:01,440
Thanks.

990
01:23:34,760 --> 01:23:36,800
Ugh!

991
01:23:51,760 --> 01:23:54,160
You lied to me.

992
01:23:56,240 --> 01:23:58,200
I'm sorry.

993
01:23:59,800 --> 01:24:01,800
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

994
01:24:01,880 --> 01:24:04,840
<i>I've been so crazy,
I don't know what's going on.</i>

995
01:24:04,840 --> 01:24:10,200
I didn't want... I don't...
don't want it to end.

996
01:24:10,160 --> 01:24:12,160
That's all.

997
01:24:13,840 --> 01:24:16,600
<i>- But you're sick. We have to go back.
- No, listen.</i>

998
01:24:16,680 --> 01:24:19,120
Can't we just pretend that, um...

999
01:24:19,200 --> 01:24:21,760
<i>- Pretend?
- Yes.</i>

1000
01:24:21,840 --> 01:24:24,880
Yeah, that it, um, um...
that I'm all right.

1001
01:24:24,880 --> 01:24:27,360
But you're not all right.
You're sick.

1002
01:24:27,400 --> 01:24:29,800
- No, no. No.
- And you're going back to the hospital.

1003
01:24:29,880 --> 01:24:32,360
- Listen to me. Do you love me?
- What?

1004
01:24:32,440 --> 01:24:36,720
Just tell me. I know it's difficult.
I'm sorry. Just tell me.

1005
01:24:36,640 --> 01:24:39,200
- Tell me.
- I don't like this.

1006
01:24:39,280 --> 01:24:41,080
All right, all right, all right.

1007
01:24:41,200 --> 01:24:43,840
I'm not going back.
I am never going back.

1008
01:24:43,920 --> 01:24:46,800
I did lie to you. I wasn't through
with the chemotherapy.

1009
01:24:46,880 --> 01:24:49,520
- What!
- Shh. Shh. My beautiful, sweet girl.

1010
01:24:49,600 --> 01:24:53,400
I'm sorry. I had to.
It was killing me.

1011
01:24:53,440 --> 01:24:58,080
You saw it.
That's why I chose you.

1012
01:24:58,080 --> 01:25:00,760
Not just to come up here
with me...

1013
01:25:00,880 --> 01:25:03,560
but to stay with me
no matter what happens.

1014
01:25:03,640 --> 01:25:05,360
- No matter what happens.
- No!

1015
01:25:05,520 --> 01:25:08,320
Shh, shh, shh!

1016
01:25:08,400 --> 01:25:11,440
Just to stay for good... or whatever.

1017
01:25:13,080 --> 01:25:17,080
Just no more hospitals.
No more treatments.

1018
01:25:17,040 --> 01:25:20,240
No more.

1019
01:25:20,240 --> 01:25:22,680
It is enough, Hilary.

1020
01:25:22,720 --> 01:25:25,520
Ten years is enough.

1021
01:25:25,600 --> 01:25:29,400
That's no life. I need a life.

1022
01:25:29,440 --> 01:25:31,720
I have a life with you.

1023
01:25:33,440 --> 01:25:36,760
- If you love me, you'll help me.
- Do what?

1024
01:25:36,760 --> 01:25:39,960
Let it happen.
Just let it happen.

1025
01:25:39,960 --> 01:25:43,320
- Let you die?
- No.

1026
01:25:46,480 --> 01:25:48,800
When you decide?

1027
01:25:48,840 --> 01:25:52,120
<i>You don't ask me or anything.
You just decided?</i>

1028
01:25:52,120 --> 01:25:55,840
And then you want me to say...
You want me...

1029
01:25:55,880 --> 01:25:58,240
You want me to tell you I love you?

1030
01:25:58,280 --> 01:26:01,840
Then you can say, "Well, great. Now
I'm gonna die and I'm gonna leave you. "

1031
01:26:01,880 --> 01:26:04,560
Hilary.

1032
01:26:04,600 --> 01:26:08,600
And you let me believe
that we had...

1033
01:26:08,520 --> 01:26:12,080
that I was part of something real
for the first time in my life.

1034
01:26:12,120 --> 01:26:14,720
And the whole goddamn thing
was a lie!

1035
01:26:14,760 --> 01:26:17,320
No, Hilary, I believed it too.

1036
01:26:19,000 --> 01:26:21,520
I thought that this time
I wouldn't get sick again.

1037
01:26:21,600 --> 01:26:25,360
<i>- I thought you could...
- What? That I could what?</i>

1038
01:26:29,080 --> 01:26:32,520
<i>Do you have any idea
what it's like for me here?</i>

1039
01:26:32,520 --> 01:26:36,600
You know, every day...

1040
01:26:36,560 --> 01:26:40,560
every fucking day I wake up
to see if you're still alive.

1041
01:26:40,520 --> 01:26:44,240
I watch to see if you eat,
to see if you shit.

1042
01:26:44,280 --> 01:26:47,040
<i>And you knew that you were
getting sick again the whole time...</i>

1043
01:26:47,120 --> 01:26:48,920
<i>and you didn't tell me.</i>

1044
01:26:49,040 --> 01:26:52,240
<i>How was I supposed to know?
Because I'm not a nurse.</i>

1045
01:26:52,240 --> 01:26:54,840
I'm not a fucking nurse!

1046
01:26:54,880 --> 01:26:57,880
You think I don't feel something
because I'm stupid?

1047
01:26:57,880 --> 01:27:00,320
Fuck you,
because I feel something!

1048
01:27:00,320 --> 01:27:02,760
I feel everything,
and I can't watch you die!

1049
01:27:56,120 --> 01:27:59,640
- Hello.
- M-Mr. Geddes, this is Hilary O'Neil.

1050
01:27:59,680 --> 01:28:02,440
- I'm your son's...
- I know exactly who you are, Miss O'Neil.

1051
01:28:02,520 --> 01:28:05,280
I must tell you
that if my son is in any danger...

1052
01:28:05,320 --> 01:28:09,080
Uh... he is.
That's why I'm calling.

1053
01:28:10,600 --> 01:28:13,800
He's very sick, and I think you
need to come get him now.

1054
01:28:13,800 --> 01:28:17,680
Yes. All right.
Where? Where is he?

1055
01:28:17,720 --> 01:28:20,720
He's, um...

1056
01:28:20,720 --> 01:28:22,760
Miss O'Neil...

1057
01:28:25,480 --> 01:28:27,280
please.

1058
01:28:27,400 --> 01:28:30,120
3 Main Street, Mendocino.

1059
01:28:30,240 --> 01:28:33,640
Okay. Okay, okay.

1060
01:28:33,600 --> 01:28:36,760
You did the right thing.

1061
01:28:36,760 --> 01:28:39,760
Oh, Victor. Shit!

1062
01:28:42,640 --> 01:28:46,360
Okay, okay.

1063
01:28:54,840 --> 01:28:57,280
Victor, Victor.

1064
01:29:06,560 --> 01:29:10,960
<i>I had the police looking for you.
I hired two detectives to look for you.</i>

1065
01:29:10,920 --> 01:29:15,640
I just don't understand why... I don't
know why you would sneak away like that.

1066
01:29:15,640 --> 01:29:17,960
<i>Do you hate me that much?</i>

1067
01:29:18,000 --> 01:29:21,440
No. No.

1068
01:29:25,240 --> 01:29:28,360
You're my father.

1069
01:29:29,520 --> 01:29:31,320
I love you.

1070
01:29:32,920 --> 01:29:35,560
<i>But I am not a boy anymore...</i>

1071
01:29:35,640 --> 01:29:39,200
and I just wanted to be alone
with Hilary, that's all.

1072
01:29:40,600 --> 01:29:42,800
All right.

1073
01:29:42,840 --> 01:29:44,880
Yes.

1074
01:29:44,920 --> 01:29:48,120
But when you're through
with the treatment.

1075
01:29:48,160 --> 01:29:53,560
I mean, Victor, God, how could you
walk away in the middle of it?

1076
01:30:03,520 --> 01:30:07,160
I wanted... her
to see me with hair.

1077
01:30:12,080 --> 01:30:14,520
So why didn't you tell me that?

1078
01:30:17,280 --> 01:30:21,000
- You think I wouldn't understand?
- Would you have let me go?

1079
01:30:23,880 --> 01:30:25,920
No.

1080
01:30:25,960 --> 01:30:28,600
Victor, believe me,
believe me, believe...

1081
01:30:28,680 --> 01:30:32,320
I would love to hide away here,
too, with a beautiful girl.

1082
01:30:32,320 --> 01:30:34,760
- It's the enchanted cottage.
- It was.

1083
01:30:34,800 --> 01:30:38,280
But I am taking you
back to the hospital now.

1084
01:30:49,720 --> 01:30:53,880
Okay. Okay, but tomorrow.

1085
01:30:53,840 --> 01:30:55,640
- No.
- I'll go back with you tomorrow.

1086
01:30:55,760 --> 01:30:57,800
- Victor, listen to me.
- There's a party tonight.

1087
01:30:57,840 --> 01:30:59,840
Well, you...

1088
01:31:01,520 --> 01:31:04,280
I have to see her one last time.

1089
01:31:07,360 --> 01:31:09,440
I have to.

1090
01:31:14,680 --> 01:31:16,480
Please.

1091
01:31:21,040 --> 01:31:23,400
All right.

1092
01:31:31,880 --> 01:31:34,000
Somebody dropped
something over there.

1093
01:31:34,040 --> 01:31:37,480
Sylvia, bring that stuff
and put it right over there.

1094
01:31:43,720 --> 01:31:47,520
I'm sorry I can't come
to your party tonight, Estelle.

1095
01:31:47,560 --> 01:31:52,560
Victor is very sick, and I had to
call his father to come get him.

1096
01:31:52,440 --> 01:31:55,520
I know. Victor called.

1097
01:31:55,480 --> 01:31:59,360
He and his father
are coming tonight.

1098
01:31:59,400 --> 01:32:04,600
You know... people think it's funny
that I buried three husbands.

1099
01:32:04,520 --> 01:32:07,000
It's a joke around here.

1100
01:32:08,840 --> 01:32:10,640
I don't know why.

1101
01:32:10,760 --> 01:32:14,000
<i>It isn't funny at all...</i>

1102
01:32:14,000 --> 01:32:19,000
<i>watching someone you love
get sick, is it?</i>

1103
01:32:18,920 --> 01:32:21,760
I don't give advice, love.

1104
01:32:25,400 --> 01:32:27,920
But if I were you...

1105
01:32:28,000 --> 01:32:30,480
I'd be at the party tonight.

1106
01:32:35,600 --> 01:32:38,080
Merry Christmas.

1107
01:33:58,880 --> 01:34:00,680
Hello. I'm Victor's father.

1108
01:34:00,800 --> 01:34:03,160
Hi. Gordon.
Nice to meet you.

1109
01:34:04,800 --> 01:34:09,200
Thank you, Miss O'Neil.
You saved his life.

1110
01:34:11,040 --> 01:34:13,680
- Is he here?
- Yes.

1111
01:34:13,760 --> 01:34:17,320
<i>Well, he was standing
right over there a second ago.</i>

1112
01:34:17,320 --> 01:34:19,560
You want to dance?
Let's dance.

1113
01:34:19,600 --> 01:34:22,720
<i>- No, I don't think I...
- Come on, let's dance.</i>

1114
01:35:12,000 --> 01:35:14,760
What's the matter?

1115
01:35:14,880 --> 01:35:17,360
Um... I'll be back.

1116
01:35:17,440 --> 01:35:19,200
Hilary...

1117
01:35:41,160 --> 01:35:42,960
Victor.

1118
01:35:55,040 --> 01:35:57,680
I'm sorry.
I had to call your father.

1119
01:36:03,400 --> 01:36:05,200
I'm going back with him.

1120
01:36:05,320 --> 01:36:07,680
<i>- To the hospital?
- Yes.</i>

1121
01:36:07,760 --> 01:36:09,840
Good.

1122
01:36:09,880 --> 01:36:12,080
They'll take care of you there.

1123
01:36:14,600 --> 01:36:17,200
Tell Gordon he better
damn well take care of you.

1124
01:36:17,280 --> 01:36:19,600
No, it's not like that.

1125
01:36:19,680 --> 01:36:23,360
I'll be going back
to Oakland soon, and...

1126
01:36:23,400 --> 01:36:25,600
and I'll visit you, if that's okay.

1127
01:36:27,480 --> 01:36:30,680
I think we should just...

1128
01:36:59,680 --> 01:37:01,520
Good-bye.

1129
01:37:13,200 --> 01:37:16,000
Well, I remember them. Of course.

1130
01:37:16,080 --> 01:37:19,080
<i>They've moved into the area,
and they would love to see you.</i>

1131
01:37:19,120 --> 01:37:21,960
<i>- Why don't you stop in and see them?
- Next time I'll do that.</i>

1132
01:37:22,040 --> 01:37:24,240
- Mr. Geddes. Hi.
- Hello.

1133
01:37:24,280 --> 01:37:26,560
I thought Victor
was going back with you.

1134
01:37:26,600 --> 01:37:28,680
He is. Tomorrow.

1135
01:37:28,720 --> 01:37:32,320
He, uh, wanted
to spend the night alone.

1136
01:37:32,360 --> 01:37:35,600
Now, don't worry.
He's safe now.

1137
01:37:37,240 --> 01:37:40,360
He said he'd call me
in the morning.

1138
01:37:40,360 --> 01:37:43,120
<i>- Thanks.
- Merry Christmas, Miss O'Neil.</i>

1139
01:37:46,520 --> 01:37:48,520
Excuse me.

1140
01:38:33,880 --> 01:38:35,760
- You running away?
- Jesus.

1141
01:38:35,880 --> 01:38:39,920
I thought that was my trick.

1142
01:38:42,960 --> 01:38:45,520
No more tricks, Hilary...

1143
01:38:45,560 --> 01:38:48,280
and no more hospitals.

1144
01:38:48,400 --> 01:38:51,200
<i>I don't want to hurt you anymore.</i>

1145
01:38:51,280 --> 01:38:53,440
I never wanted to hurt you.

1146
01:38:53,480 --> 01:38:56,560
<i>You know, you are the first person...</i>

1147
01:38:56,560 --> 01:39:00,080
in 10 years that made me
forget that I was sick.

1148
01:39:02,480 --> 01:39:05,240
I just wanted
to stay here with you.

1149
01:39:06,520 --> 01:39:09,840
<i>- To make love with you.
- Then where are you going?</i>

1150
01:39:09,840 --> 01:39:13,400
You gonna hide somewhere
till you die?

1151
01:39:13,400 --> 01:39:16,720
I can't let you do that, Victor.
I can't let you give up.

1152
01:39:16,760 --> 01:39:19,360
I gave up when you left me.

1153
01:39:19,440 --> 01:39:22,480
No, you didn't.
You gave up before I left.

1154
01:39:24,240 --> 01:39:28,560
Hilary... I don't want
to be sick anymore.

1155
01:39:28,560 --> 01:39:31,600
I know. That's why I want you
to come back with me.

1156
01:39:31,600 --> 01:39:33,160
<i>- I can't.
- Why?</i>

1157
01:39:33,280 --> 01:39:37,080
<i>- I'll drive you to the hospital. I'll carry you.
- I cannot do it.</i>

1158
01:39:37,120 --> 01:39:38,280
<i>- Why?
- I can't do it.</i>

1159
01:39:38,360 --> 01:39:40,400
<i>- Tell me why.
- Because.</i>

1160
01:39:40,480 --> 01:39:43,080
Because I am afraid.

1161
01:39:43,200 --> 01:39:44,960
Afraid of what?

1162
01:39:45,080 --> 01:39:47,480
Of hoping!

1163
01:39:55,160 --> 01:39:58,160
It hurts to be around you, Hilary...

1164
01:39:58,160 --> 01:39:59,960
because...

1165
01:40:01,680 --> 01:40:05,800
you make me want to live...
so much.

1166
01:40:05,760 --> 01:40:08,200
Then live, Victor.

1167
01:40:08,240 --> 01:40:10,560
You don't know
what's gonna happen.

1168
01:40:10,640 --> 01:40:13,840
You don't know when
you're gonna die. Nobody does.

1169
01:40:13,840 --> 01:40:17,680
But we have right now.
So fight, Victor. Live with me.

1170
01:40:17,720 --> 01:40:19,520
- I can't.
- Live with me.

1171
01:40:19,640 --> 01:40:22,000
I can't do that.

1172
01:40:22,040 --> 01:40:24,920
Look at you.

1173
01:40:26,680 --> 01:40:31,040
You are so... young...

1174
01:40:31,000 --> 01:40:34,240
and so beautiful and smart.

1175
01:40:34,240 --> 01:40:39,120
You can do anything, Hilary.
Anything you want to do.

1176
01:40:39,120 --> 01:40:41,600
Why do you want to do this?

1177
01:40:41,680 --> 01:40:43,720
Because I love you.

1178
01:40:43,760 --> 01:40:48,400
And if you come back with me
to the hospital and fight for us...

1179
01:40:48,400 --> 01:40:51,640
if you fight for us,
I will never leave you, Victor.

1180
01:40:51,640 --> 01:40:54,840
But you have to fight.
And if you get well...

1181
01:40:54,840 --> 01:40:57,720
when you get well...
I- I'll be there with you.

1182
01:40:57,760 --> 01:41:01,560
And if you, if you die,
I'll hold your hand.

1183
01:41:03,360 --> 01:41:06,200
I'll hold your hand.

1184
01:41:06,280 --> 01:41:10,520
And the last thing
you'd ever see would be me...

1185
01:41:10,480 --> 01:41:12,480
because I love you.

1186
01:41:15,040 --> 01:41:17,840
I do.

1187
01:41:19,400 --> 01:41:21,720
Oh, God.

1188
01:41:30,880 --> 01:41:32,680
I love you.

